24:10.080 --> 24:14.900
Jack Chalker's reputation was greatly enhanced by the popular, well-world series of novels.

24:14.900 --> 24:20.480
Now he's at work on a new series, one which will have four books in it entitled The Four Lords of the Diamond.

24:21.280 --> 24:23.060
Two novels have been published so far.

24:23.320 --> 24:26.100
The first is called Lilith and the second Cerberus.

24:26.840 --> 24:28.240
Chalker comments on the story.

24:30.080 --> 24:35.760
It has a tremendous number of the elements that I have become known for.

24:36.000 --> 24:38.060
It has a lot of new material as well.

24:38.260 --> 24:39.800
It has a lot of political commentary.

24:40.460 --> 24:42.620
It has a lot of social commentary in it.

24:42.620 --> 24:51.880
It has also slam bang action, Machiavellian intrigue and everything else because nobody's going to read your message if you don't entertain first.

24:53.320 --> 24:56.280
As Chalker says, the books have a lot of excitement in them.

24:56.580 --> 25:04.500
In the opening pages of Lilith, the first book in the series, a tremendously powerful alien robot penetrates a top secret military installation on Earth.

25:04.760 --> 25:09.420
The robot's discovered, but he escapes and heads for a planetary system called the Warden Diamond.

25:09.420 --> 25:11.680
The Earth government sends its top agent.

25:13.400 --> 25:19.940
These are four worlds in one system that are basically a prison planet series.

25:21.580 --> 25:28.520
You get dropped on there and the foundation idea which appealed to me an awful lot is

25:28.520 --> 25:36.980
an alien race discovers us before we discover them, decides that it can't win a war against us.

25:36.980 --> 25:44.480
Maybe they're just not as many of them or there's technological problems or something like that.

25:45.200 --> 25:53.040
So they study us and study us and they discover that as in all human societies there is this massive criminal syndicate.

25:54.000 --> 26:05.700
And that this criminal syndicate leaders are mostly imprisoned for life on the four lords of the Warden Diamond.

26:06.280 --> 26:07.480
These four worlds.

26:08.020 --> 26:18.740
So what the aliens do is they contact these bitter super crux and they take out a contract on human civilization.

26:20.620 --> 26:24.080
The agent can't land on any of the four worlds of the Warden Diamond.

26:24.680 --> 26:28.940
A tiny organism on these worlds enters the body and makes a person a virtual prisoner.

26:29.380 --> 26:34.020
Right. If you try to leave you die a painful death. There seems to be no cure for it either.

26:34.020 --> 26:41.540
So what the agent does is have his personality implanted into four separate bodies and these bodies are sent to each of the worlds.

26:41.920 --> 26:45.660
And he monitors what is happening through a computer hookup orbiting the Warden system.

26:46.800 --> 26:59.260
Part of what the book is about is that we have a sort of surrogate him down on each of these worlds who starts off pretty much are almost identical to him.

27:00.020 --> 27:05.240
And he's following this whole thing with his whole system of values, beliefs and so on.

27:05.740 --> 27:10.980
And he's watching these surrogates change into quite different people.

27:12.040 --> 27:17.500
And it begins to eat away at his own sense of values, his own sense of duty.

27:18.560 --> 27:28.540
As a matter of fact in the third book he begins to realize that the people who sent him there on this mission anticipated this.

27:28.540 --> 27:39.380
And that his computer detective aide who he has dialogues with and discusses everything with, maybe more than that it may be something of a watchdog.

27:41.380 --> 27:48.580
Chalker promises an exciting ending when the agent struggles with his own newly discovered values with the computer and with the aliens.

27:48.580 --> 27:54.480
I don't like cop-outs, I don't like stringing people along and then not delivering.

27:57.000 --> 28:06.300
You will get real, I don't know whether you can say flesh and blood but something, aliens and whatever they're made of.

28:07.340 --> 28:17.640
You will meet the aliens, you will have a face down and the solution to the whole thing and exactly what's going on is quite bizarre.

28:17.640 --> 28:19.460
And I don't think anyone's going to figure it out.

